    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date><sic>febry</sic> 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5610</date>.</p>
            <p>To the <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Revd. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I must beg leave to refer<lb/> you to my note of the <date>18<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> of November</date> last,<lb/> in which I requested you to
                insert our Circular<lb/> 'in the <hi rend="underline">next</hi> number of the
                Occident'; meaning, of<lb/> course, only that of <date>December</date> and not any
                subsequent<lb/> one. Although I found it again in the <date>January</date>
                number,<lb/> I thought that it had been reinserted, either from<lb/> an
                extraordinary consideration on your part, of which,<lb/> however the committee had
                not the slightest expectation,<lb/> or by a mistake, which you would discover,
                previously<lb/> to the publication of the <sic>february</sic> number. To my<lb/>
                surprise, however, I find it also in this, and must,<lb/> therefore, respectfully
                call your attention to this error;<lb/> as the committee could not consider
                themselves bound<lb/> to pay for more than the one insertion which they have
                ordered.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I am with regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your most obt sert.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">G Coznanski</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Chairman.</p>
            <p>Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Permit me to avail myself of this occasion,<lb/> for the purpose of
                inquiring, whether my name has,<lb/> accidentally, been omitted or I have overlooked
                it</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>among the names of those of your subscribers, who<lb/> have paid up their
                subscription to the <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> of April</date><lb/> last, to
                which day I paid mine to <persName>Mr S. Hart</persName> in<lb/> this city on the
                        <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date> last. I should have paid it
                when<lb/> due, had the Bill then been presented to me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Very respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">your obt sert.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">G Coznanski</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>To the <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>
                    <hi rend="underline">Pa</hi>
                </placeName>
            </p>
